title: For Sale:  Pre-Ban Ruger Mini 14 with Side Folding Stock .223
postcontent: Ruger's Mini 14 is a classic. Taking the heavy steel and wood from rifles of yesteryear, it's an M14 that shrunk in the wash. Because it's a scaled down battle rifle, it handles the little .223 Remington round perfectly. Ruger has offered the Mini 14 is a variety of configurations: stainless finish, synthetic stocks, tactical models, other calibers. The coolest, by far, is the side-folding stock models of the 1980s (famously adopted for service by television's "A-Team").The serial number on this example puts it as having been manufactured in 1985. The more modern telescoping stock models are all fine and good, but there's nothing like folding the stock, locking it down, and ending up with a nice, little package. And the rifle fires with the stock folded, too!This Mini has been previously loved and improved upon.
